On the online Ubuntu 22.04.5 VM

1. Plug in the thumb drive and find it

lsblk

Assume it shows as /dev/sdb1.

Mount it:

sudo mkdir -p /mnt/usb
sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt/usb

2. Make a folder for Ubuntu 24.04 OpenSSH packages

mkdir -p ~/offline-openssh-24.04
cd ~/offline-openssh-24.04

3. Create a clean Ubuntu 24.04 apt download environment

mkdir -p apt-noble/{etc/apt/sources.list.d,etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d,var/lib/apt/lists/partial,var/cache/apt/archives/partial,var/lib/dpkg}
touch apt-noble/var/lib/dpkg/status
cp /usr/share/keyrings/ubuntu-archive-keyring.gpg apt-noble/etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/

Create the Ubuntu 24.04 repo list:

cat > apt-noble/etc/apt/sources.list <<'EOF'
deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu noble main restricted universe multiverse
deb http://archive.ubuntu.com/ubuntu noble-updates main restricted universe multiverse
deb http://security.ubuntu.com/ubuntu noble-security main restricted universe multiverse
EOF

4. Download openssh-server and all needed dependencies for Ubuntu 24.04

sudo apt-get \
  -o Dir::Etc::sourcelist="$PWD/apt-noble/etc/apt/sources.list" \
  -o Dir::Etc::sourceparts="$PWD/apt-noble/etc/apt/sources.list.d" \
  -o Dir::State="$PWD/apt-noble/var/lib/apt" \
  -o Dir::Cache="$PWD/apt-noble/var/cache/apt" \
  -o Dir::State::status="$PWD/apt-noble/var/lib/dpkg/status" \
  update

Then download:

sudo apt-get \
  -o Dir::Etc::sourcelist="$PWD/apt-noble/etc/apt/sources.list" \
  -o Dir::Etc::sourceparts="$PWD/apt-noble/etc/apt/sources.list.d" \
  -o Dir::State="$PWD/apt-noble/var/lib/apt" \
  -o Dir::Cache="$PWD/apt-noble/var/cache/apt" \
  -o Dir::State::status="$PWD/apt-noble/var/lib/dpkg/status" \
  --download-only install -y openssh-server

5. Copy the .deb files to the thumb drive

mkdir -p /mnt/usb/openssh-server-ubuntu-24.04
cp apt-noble/var/cache/apt/archives/*.deb /mnt/usb/openssh-server-ubuntu-24.04/
sync

Unmount:

sudo umount /mnt/usb

⸻

On the offline Ubuntu 24.04 VM on ESXi

1. Attach the USB drive to the VM

In ESXi Host Client:

VM → Edit settings → Add USB device

Then boot/log into the Ubuntu 24.04 VM.

2. Mount the USB drive

lsblk

Assume it is /dev/sdb1.

sudo mkdir -p /mnt/usb
sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt/usb

3. Copy packages locally

mkdir -p ~/openssh-offline
cp /mnt/usb/openssh-server-ubuntu-24.04/*.deb ~/openssh-offline/
cd ~/openssh-offline

4. Install the packages

sudo dpkg -i ./*.deb

If it complains about order/dependencies, run it once more:

sudo dpkg -i ./*.deb

5. Enable and start SSH

sudo systemctl enable ssh
sudo systemctl start ssh
sudo systemctl status ssh

6. Check the VM IP

ip a

Then from another machine on the same network:

ssh username@VM_IP_ADDRESS

Example:

ssh kevin@10.10.10.101

Important: do not use Ubuntu 22.04 .deb packages on the Ubuntu 24.04 VM. Use the noble/24.04 packages as shown above.
